<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoanad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goanad</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:20:22 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: About your statement Graffe..?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><br>
I think the common cry from the masses of wizards should be that ONE of those TWO supposedly &quot;dead horses&quot; needs to be rezzed. I would prefer the mana regen side because I really have to agree with Graffe's initial observation that DAMAGE = AGGRO. <br>
<br>
What mana regen would do is allow the wizard to take good tactics and do them more often than sitting out every other pull because your &quot;low mana light&quot; went on after the last fight. The more times you can stand up and take the mob from the 50% HP stage to the run stage, and thereby bypassing that frenzy stage when the mob really lets the melees have it, the better you will be looked upon by any given group. Even with the chanter doing traffic duty, there still one or two mobs that are slapping your meat shields around. With better mana regen you can be there to help them out in a very profound manner. <br>
<br>
My total levels achieved is 66 in EQ spread out among three characters. I've seen battle and good grouping strats from everyside of the ball, so to speak. Offensively with a Wizard for 26 levels, up front banging away with a warrior to the 20th level, and then lately, crowd control and buffing\debuffing with my near 20th chanter. So, I've been the OOM wizard AND the tank whose heard the OOM cries of the wizard who couldnt help me with the mob in the frenzy stage as it hit me for significantly more HPs than during the early stages of the fight. <br>
<br>
I just hope that one of those &quot;dead horses&quot; is rezzed, saddled up and made truly trail worthy so I didn't waste 26 levels on a wizard who is not group friendly for the aforestated reasons. <br>
<br>
