Summon Mob<br>
Bannish Mob<br>
<br>
The 1st would summon a targeted mob to you - i.e. You shall not Evade me a_mob_01! I believe this game mechanic was meant for teleporters - the new wizard definition- and would bring a great new attribute to our class (I am positive this would make us wanted in groups). Face it, no one cares about our damage because we will always be inferior to a mana-less tank. Nothing will change that (besides a total rehall of damage spells and better caster gear for mid range characters). It would have a casting range and maybe a line of sight needed (as the game mechanics now function). I would LOVE this spell.<br>
The second line would bannish a mob back to its bindpoint, removing all agro unless the people were still in agro range (i.e. along Mez agro lines - although would have to be more reliable). Also would make us useful for crowd control as well. I don't think this steps on chanter's toes. Maybe it would Kill the mob as well -a.k.a disinegrate sub 60 wizards.<br>
-Aleolin Darkmoon<br>
