<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=3270.topic">pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffe...3270.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--></font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Sorcerer</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1:46:08 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Total Damage Per Hour</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Wizards have to do the same damage per full bar of mana/recovery as a Magician, Rogue, Monk etc.  Why?  Because the melee classes don't have to use mana to do their damage, and because the Magician offers the damage with two out of three irresistable sources, and the damage is steady and long term.<br>
<br>
Wizards would do their damage fast and furious, and be out or low on mana, while the Magician can burn and med while damage shields and pets continue to contribute.  Magicians freak out when they hear this, all they see is &quot;same damage over time and less in the short term! AEIIII!!!&quot; but they haven't thought it through to see the reality of the issue.<br>
<br>
Honestly, putting a superfast, lower damage, low mana efficiency (half the normal blast that level, for example) for emergencies is a good idea for a series of blasts.  This could be every 2 spell circles.  The logic behind this is the shot you use in the absolute emergency, something to uncork that is VERY fast, like 2 seconds or shorter.<br>
<br>
Then add in a HUGE blast every 2 spell circles, alternating with the fast emergency blast above.  This blast would have a LONG casting time (fury of ice, fury of fire, etc... takes 6 seconds to cast at level 20, as an example... slower as you go up levels) doing 1 1/2-2 times the damage of the blast that level.  The mana efficiency could be terrible for this too, the idea is that it is for that &quot;MUST DIE NOW&quot; or closing shot, but worthless in soloing.  This would have a long recast time on it and perhaps a reagent.<br>
<br>
Lures at lower levels of course, something like Enticement of Frost at level 20 that does 85 damage but is nearly irresistable and costs Force Shock level mana.  This would allow people to contribute against things over the level cap.<br>
<br>
See how that works?  3 more TYPES of blast to add to the aresenal that don't have a real major effect on our damage output, but would give us TOOLS for specific types of situations and encounters.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>2:23:47 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Total Damage Per Hour</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I suggested something similar on the sony boards right before they were closed, and got the same &quot;but 6 wizards..&quot; nonesense.<br>
