Channel Fire, Channel Ice, Channel Magic, I had full spell descriptions but they were deleted with the board and the details aren't important anyway.<br>
<br>
Wizards should be the artillery. The artillery cannot stand alone, but the infantry should WANT artillery. (and as a vet of the 101st, I can tell you in RL they do, believe me) I think it is obvious Wizards were designed to be the artillery, but somewhere along the way VI got very VERY confused.<br>
<br>
They got confused because they couldn't figure out a way to make the artillery want to keep the infantry around. It was simple, these spells would do it, and there are many other ideas. But for some reason the solution was beyond them.<br>
<br>
So now what we have is a case where the infantry has no use for the artillery because they do better without it!!<br>
<br>
That is patently fup-ucked.<br>
<br>
I WOULD GIVE UP *ALL* PORTS TO BE THE ARTILLERY LIKE WIZARDS ARE SUPPOSED TO BE.<br>
<br>
Necros and Mages were designed to be solo classes, and are, but turned out to be bigger damage dealers. (granted against some mobs, being mana battery is no fun, but at least it's a DESIRED ROLE)<br>
<br>
Clerics and Warriors are pretty much what they are supposed to be.<br>
<br>
Shaman and Enchanters are pretty much what they were supposed to be, as are the hybrids and rogues.<br>
<br>
Druids can do everything, and track on top.<br>
<br>
I don't want to see one other class nerfed.<br>
<br>
Wizards are supposed to be all offense, no defense. You don't send artillery alone to fight a battle. But you also should always want artillery when you can get it.<br>
<br>
I just want my role *in* the battle.<br>
<br>
Not taxi to and from the battle.<br>
<br>
